sudo apt install qemu-user 

# run ARM binary 
qemu-arm -L /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/  main 

# In order to run ELF with couple of libraries: 
qemu-arm /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/lib/ld-linux-armhf.so.3 --library-path "/usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/lib:../:../../../../openssl" ./sample 

# debug with qemu 
port 12345: 
qemu-arm -g 12345 -L /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/  main 

and in another terminal:
gdb-multiarch 
set solib-absolute-prefix /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/ 
target remote 127.0.0.1:12345 
x/10i $pc 

you need to set a breakpoint on a function that you know that will be triggered, and then when it will be triggered you will be able to display disassembly. 
